#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:2
msgid "fish_add_path - add to the path"
msgstr "fish_add_path - 增添路徑"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:7
msgid ""
"fish_add_path path ...\n"
"fish_add_path [(-g | --global) | (-U | --universal) | (-P | --path)] [(-m | "
"--move)] [(-a | --append) | (-p | --prepend)] [(-v | --verbose) | (-n | --"
"dry-run)] PATHS ..."
msgstr ""
"fish_add_path path ...\n"
"fish_add_path [(-g | --global) | (-U | --universal) | (-P | --path)] [(-m | "
"--move)] [(-a | --append) | (-p | --prepend)] [(-v | --verbose) | (-n | --"
"dry-run)] PATHS ..."

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr "描述"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:16
msgid ""
":program:`fish_add_path` is a simple way to add more directories to fish's :"
"envvar:`PATH`. It does this by adding the directories either to :envvar:"
"`fish_user_paths` or directly to :envvar:`PATH` (if the ``--path`` switch is "
"given)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:18
msgid ""
"It is (by default) safe to use :program:`fish_add_path` in config.fish, or "
"it can be used once, interactively, and the paths will stay in future "
"because of :ref:`universal variables <variables-universal>`. This is a \"do "
"what I mean\" style command - it tries to do the right thing by default, and "
"follow your lead on what you have already set up (e.g. by using a global :"
"envvar:`fish_user_paths` if you have that already). If you need more "
"control, consider modifying the variable yourself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:20
msgid ""
"Directories are normalized with :doc:`realpath <realpath>`. Trailing slashes "
"are ignored and relative paths are made absolute (but symlinks are not "
"resolved). If a directory is already included, it is not added again and "
"stays in the same place unless the ``--move`` switch is given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:22
msgid ""
"Directories are added in the order they are given, and they are prepended to "
"the path unless ``--append`` is given. If $fish_user_paths is used, that "
"means they are last in $fish_user_paths, which is itself prepended to :"
"envvar:`PATH`, so they still stay ahead of the system paths. If the ``--"
"path`` option is used, the paths are appended/prepended to :envvar:`PATH` "
"directly, so this doesn't happen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:24
msgid ""
"With ``--path``, because :envvar:`PATH` must be a global variable instead of "
"a universal one, the changes won't persist, so those calls need to be stored "
"in :ref:`config.fish <configuration>`. This also applies to :envvar:"
"`fish_user_paths` if you make it global (for instance by passing ``--"
"global``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:26
msgid ""
"If no directory is new, the variable (:envvar:`fish_user_paths` or :envvar:"
"`PATH`) is not set again or otherwise modified, so variable handlers are not "
"triggered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:28
msgid ""
"If an argument is not an existing directory, ``fish_add_path`` ignores it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:31
msgid "Options"
msgstr "選項"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:33
msgid "**-a** or **--append**"
msgstr "**-a** 或 **--append**"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:34
msgid "Add directories to the *end* of the variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:36
msgid "**-p** or **--prepend**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:37
msgid "Add directories to the *front* of the variable (this is the default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:39
msgid "**-g** or **--global**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:40
msgid "Use a global :envvar:`fish_user_paths`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:42
msgid "**-U** or **--universal**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:43
msgid ""
"Use a universal :envvar:`fish_user_paths` - this is the default if it "
"doesn't already exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:45
msgid "**-P** or **--path**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:46
msgid "Manipulate :envvar:`PATH` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:48
msgid "**-m** or **--move**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:49
msgid ""
"Move already-included directories to the place they would be added - by "
"default they would be left in place and not added again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:51
msgid "**-v** or **--verbose**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:52
msgid ""
"Print the :doc:`set <set>` command used, and some more warnings, like when a "
"path is skipped because it doesn't exist or is not a directory. Verbose mode "
"is automatically enabled when fish_add_path is used interactively and the "
"output goes to the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:55
msgid "**-n** or **--dry-run**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:56
msgid "Print the ``set`` command that would be used without executing it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:58
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:59
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr "顯示此指令的幫助資訊。"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:61
msgid ""
"If ``--move`` is used, it may of course lead to the path swapping order, so "
"you should be careful doing that in config.fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:65
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/fish_add_path.rst:70
msgid ""
"# I just installed mycoolthing and need to add it to the path to use it.\n"
"# It is at /opt/mycoolthing/bin/mycoolthing,\n"
"# so let's add the directory: /opt/mycoolthing/bin.\n"
"> fish_add_path /opt/mycoolthing/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I want my ~/.local/bin to be checked first,\n"
"# even if it was already added.\n"
"> fish_add_path -m ~/.local/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I prefer using a global fish_user_paths\n"
"# This isn't saved automatically, I need to add this to config.fish\n"
"# if I want it to stay.\n"
"> fish_add_path -g ~/.local/bin ~/.otherbin /usr/local/sbin\n"
"\n"
"# I want to append to the entire $PATH because this directory contains "
"fallbacks\n"
"# This needs --path/-P because otherwise it appends to $fish_user_paths,\n"
"# which is added to the front of $PATH.\n"
"> fish_add_path --append --path /opt/fallback/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I want to add the bin/ directory of my current $PWD (say /home/nemo/)\n"
"# -v/--verbose shows what fish_add_path did.\n"
"> fish_add_path -v bin/\n"
"set fish_user_paths /home/nemo/bin /usr/bin /home/nemo/.local/bin\n"
"\n"
"# I have installed ruby via homebrew\n"
"> fish_add_path /usr/local/opt/ruby/bin"
msgstr ""
